node.text:
In celebration and anticipation of @aftertherainbook, I sat down today with my friend, Lisa (@_lisaolivera) to discuss moving through our pain vs. ignoring it, self-trust, and finding ways to reshape our narrative as we heal and grow.
.
.
After the Rain is out on 10/13! Pre-order at the link in my bio.

node.text:
Affirmations for us:

You will and can return to yourself.
Healing might feel like it's too much to bear—that's okay. Remember that you are built for it.
Self-love is an act of healing and an act of blooming inside of your body.
If it doesn't elevate or support your growth, I would like you to consider letting it go.

If you feel like you want to give up, hold on a little tighter. If you feel like you can't do it, lean into self-belief a little harder. 

Community, I see you. Share this with whoever you think may need it.

The word “Chosen” has been coming up A LOT in my conversations, in my writing practice, in my fear + uncertainty, and in my self-inquiry. I wanted to get a community conversation going here on being chosen, answering our call, saying yes to our heart’s work or desires even if it’s scary.
.
.
Looking forward to the comments here and leaning into this deeper w/ y’all.

Leave a comment below. I love reading your reflections!

Community Updates:

1. Folks have asked for one more writing to heal course this year. Before I start my teacher residency, I’ll be offering my last 4-week online course called BEGIN AGAIN. As always, it’ll be self-paced. You can get on the waitlist at the link in my bio. Registration opens next Sunday. The price is the same as always, $49.99 for 4 weeks together.

2. A community newsletter with new journal questions goes out tomorrow. It’s been a while since I sent one out—look out for that!

3. I’m on TikToK now. I’m not sure how to use it that well (lol) but I’ll be doing tea time meditations, Breathwork exercises, and gentle reminders on there. My username is: ALEXELLEONTIKTOK

Happy Sunday!

node.text:
I remember when I used to think I was a nobody…

Now I'm living in my purpose—liberated and rooted in self-love.

What changed? I did.

Change started with a choice not to allow:
settling
self-loathing
daddy/mommy issues
trauma
low vibrational behavior/relationships
mental health challenges
and pain

be the place where I rested.

For years, I made a home out of my hurt. For years, I struggled to find my way, my footing, myself. One thing that was consistent in my life was me. My ah-ha moment was waking up to self-value + self-worth.

If you've read @aftertherainbook, you know quite a bit about my story and how I got to where I am in my healing. My healing has been my sacred choice. If you've been in community with me for a while, you're familiar with that statement.

For anyone struggling right now, no matter your life walk, I hope you trust that joy is an option—even after deep pain. I hope you remember that self-healing and emotional clarity is an option. It may feel hard as hell today—and that's OK. Beginning again can start tomorrow.

Over the past year, I've committed myself to deeper healing via learning and teaching. Last week I completed my Breathwork Teacher Training. Starting at the end of this year, I'll be a teacher in
residence at an amazing retreat center in Arizona. I've worked so hard to get to a place where self-belief overshadowed self-doubt and external negative chatter. Healing is a daily practice. I am looking forward to serving this community and beyond through breathwork and writing practice. I'm looking forward to sharing space and stories. 

I remember when I used to think I was a nobody.

Now I'm committed to my purpose—liberated and rooted in healing.

If you're reading this and feeling lost, you are not alone. Don't give up on yourself. You can heal. You can grow through the pain. You can flourish. 

Community: What is your sacred choice? 

#healthychanges / #mindsetmatters / 
#personalgrowth / #selfnurture / #healing

A reminder for today + the week ahead.

Kindness is not to be confused with:
-being passive
-having no boundaries
-tolerating unhealthy behavior
-letting people belittle you

You can be loving, kind, understanding, and compassionate without letting folks treat you poorly. Protecting your peace and space also means being very clear about what you will and will not tolerate.

Community: How are you protecting your peace this week?

node.text:
Ruminating on my past kept me from moving forward for years. Staying stuck in the cycles of negative self-talk kept me from being my best self. As I started to grow and learn more about the relationship I wanted to have with myself, I became committed to living a life that didn't hold me hostage or stuck in shame. Mistakes, shortcomings, and failures happen—that is a part of our human experience. We cannot avoid them, but we can grow from them. Each misstep taught me resilience. Choosing not to stay stuck in the past gave me the permission I needed to grow forward and do better.
 
My #oathtoself of the week is: I am not my past—moving forward is the future.

Community: What have you learned about moving forward and not staying stuck in the past?
 
 
Join me over the next 12 weeks in creating meaningful affirmations. This series is made in collaboration with @icelandicprovisions. Head over to their page to watch this week's affirmation meditation produced by @rachealweathers_. It's pretty amazing!

This is Oaths to Self. A series of personal oaths that will inspire perseverance, encourage optimism, and reignite resilience.

Together, @icelandicprovisions and I, hope that this series brings strength to both your body and mind. 
 
Throughout the year, we will be releasing 12 Oaths to Self! Starting next Monday, on @icelandicprovisions, you'll find words of affirmation and mini-meditations to start your week. Be sure to follow their page, so you don't miss them! 

Y'all know I love seeing your personal reflections, too. So feel free to share your own #OathstoSelf and tag us.

You can also add and reshare any of the Oaths to your stories or feed (tag @icelandicprovisions + me + #oathstoself) for a chance to win an Icelandic Provisions Skyr prize kit.

See you next Monday!
